{
  "texts": [
    "The XORed yield of the F task is essentially rotated by 1 byte.",
    "The computation function of the algorithm incorporates an XOR operation with subkeys, an 8×4 S-box layer, and permutation shuffling of 4-bit words.The key schedule involves the use of two additional S-boxes that differ from those employed in the Feistel function.",
    "LBlock is defenseless against impossible differential attacks for 21 rounds of LBLOCK, related-key attacks, zero-correlation attacks for 22 rounds, and integral attacks for 22 rounds [67,68,69].ITUbee: ITUbee is a highly efficient software cipher with a code size of 586 bytes and a total execution time of 2937 cycles.",
    "This version of encryption is considered to be the most compact.",
    "The key and block sizes are identical (80-bit)."
  ]
